cs.NI, cs.DS, cs.SI, cs.IT, cs.PF 

Reasoning: 
1. cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) - The paper focuses on analyzing LRU caches operating under the Shot Noise requests Model (SNM), which was proposed to better capture the characteristics of Video on Demand (VoD) traffic. This falls under the domain of networking and internet architecture. 
2. cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) - The paper deals with analyzing the performance of LRU caches, which is a classic problem in data structures and algorithms. 
3. cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) - The paper discusses the hit probability in tandem networks of caches, which can be seen as a social and information network problem. 
4. cs.IT (Information Theory) - The paper provides a large deviation principle, a law of large numbers and a central limit theorem for the cache eviction time, which are concepts from information theory. 
5. cs.PF (Performance) - The paper analyzes the performance of LRU caches under the SNM, which falls under the domain of performance evaluation.
